                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6265: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-15T14:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1925—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 15—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>229. My 226, June 14, 4 p.m. Consul general at Hankow reports British and
                    Japanese consulates and British municipal building at Kiukiang looted and bank
                    of Taiwan burned. State of affairs in Chungking is serious and situation at
                    Hankow is becoming more tense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
